      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Terrific race to end and sticking with the speedy ROCK REVOLUTION (5) who led and was run down late by ICHIBAN this course and distance last time. Meets the winner 1.5kg better and that run was off a little break after racing over 2000m in Alice Springs. Fitter and has a great record over this course and distance. Take catching. REMATCH (2) was having his first try in this area when fifth over 1300m but strips fitter and will relish the extra ground. Has yet to miss the frame in five second-up runs. VANGUARD LEGEND (4) was fourth in the ICHIBAN race and is drawn better this time. Great record here and should feature. HETTINGER (3) has a top record over the course and distance and looks hard to beat on his best form. ICHIBAN (1) races handy and lifted strongly to score last time over a few of these. More weight but hard to knock and should be in the finish again.",
